10-25 CMD COMMANDS:dir - shows files and folders
cd .. - go back one folder
cd Desktop - open Desktop folder
mkdir test - create folder named test
rmdir test - delete folder test
del file.txt - delete file
copy file.txt copy.txt - copy file
move file.txt Desktop - move file to Desktop
ren file.txt new.txt - rename file
cls - clear screen
systeminfo - show system details
tasklist - show running programs
taskkill /IM notepad.exe /F - close Notepad
shutdown /s /t 0 - shut down immediately
shutdown /r /t 0 - restart immediately
date - show date
time - show time
ipconfig - show IP address
ping google.com - test internet connection
tracert google.com - show route to website
netstat - show network connections
nslookup google.com - find website IP
chkdsk - check disk
sfc /scannow - repair system files
diskpart - open disk management tool
